This paper deals with machine learning algorithms for learning and evaluating conditional density estimates over continuous variables. It presents Bayesian network structure-learning algorithms that employ tree-based conditional density representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper deals with learning and evaluating algorithms. Additionally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.ST (Statistics) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with modeling joint probability distributions over many variables.
